- 'drenched the most' refers to the highest total precipitation;
- 'New Year's Day 2022' corresponds to the date '2022-01-01';
- 'saw rain that day' implies precipitation was greater than 0 inches;

sql:
SELECT station_name, installation_date
FROM weather_stations
ORDER BY installation_date DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'stormiest whispers of moisture' refers to the maximum humidity recorded; 
- 'beacons' refers to the weather stations;
- 'identities' include station codes and names;
- 'homes' refer to the locations of the stations;
- 'geographical coordinates' refer to latitude and longitude;
- 'heights above sea level' refer to elevation;
- 'channels through which they share their findings' refer to contact emails;
- 'times of their birth and last health check-up' refer to installation dates and last maintenance dates.

- "active users" refers to users with a status of 'active';
- "checked into weather data last year" means they accessed the data between '2023-01-01' and '2023-12-31';
- "average high temp" refers to the average maximum temperature recorded at the stations they accessed.
